# Delta Learn Backend

Django 6 + DRF + SQLite backend for the Delta Learn platform.

## Architecture

```
Delta-Learn-Backend/
├── delta_learn/          # Django project (settings, urls, wsgi)
├── chapters/             # Core app: Subject, Chapter, Question, Takeaway, Highlight, Note, StagedRequest
├── users/                # Auth app: register, login (JWT), /me
├── fixtures/             # JSON seed data exported from the original React app
└── manage.py
```

## Models (chapters app)

| Model          | Key fields                                                                 |
|----------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Subject        | slug (unique), name, description, accent_color, order                     |
| Chapter        | subject FK, chapter_number, part, title, subtitle, order                  |
| Question       | chapter FK, order, question, difficulty, tldr, answer, points (JSON), diagram, diagram2, table_data (JSON), followup |
| Takeaway       | chapter FK, order, content (HTML)                                         |
| Highlight      | user FK, chapter FK, question_index, text, color (yellow/green/blue/pink) |
| Note           | user FK, subject FK (nullable), chapter FK (nullable), content, ai_summary |
| StagedRequest  | operation (create/update/delete), target_model, target_id, payload (JSON), status (pending/approved/rejected), requested_by FK, reviewed_by FK, review_note, created_at, reviewed_at |
| EmailTopic     | subject FK, title, keywords (JSON), source (chapter/web/manual), chapter FK (nullable), is_active, created_at |
| SentHistory    | subscription FK, topic FK, sent_at, questions_json (JSON — stores AI content for past emails) |

## API Endpoints

### Public (no auth)
- `GET /api/subjects/` — list all subjects with chapter_count and written_count
- `GET /api/subjects/{slug}/` — subject detail with ordered chapter list
- `GET /api/subjects/{slug}/chapters/{number}/` — full chapter with nested questions + takeaways

### Auth (`/api/auth/`)
- `POST /api/auth/register/` — create account (username, email, password)
- `POST /api/auth/login/` — returns JWT access + refresh tokens
- `POST /api/auth/token/refresh/` — refresh access token
- `GET /api/auth/me/` — current user profile (requires Bearer token)

### Admin CRUD (`/api/manage/` — staff only)
- `GET/POST /api/manage/subjects/` — list/create subjects
- `GET/PUT/PATCH/DELETE /api/manage/subjects/{slug}/` — subject detail CRUD
- `GET/POST /api/manage/chapters/` — list/create chapters
- `GET/PUT/PATCH/DELETE /api/manage/chapters/{id}/` — chapter detail CRUD
- `GET/POST /api/manage/questions/` — list/create questions
- `GET/PUT/PATCH/DELETE /api/manage/questions/{id}/` — question detail CRUD
- `GET/POST /api/manage/takeaways/` — list/create takeaways
- `GET/PUT/PATCH/DELETE /api/manage/takeaways/{id}/` — takeaway detail CRUD

### Staged Requests (`/api/staged/` — authenticated, admin approves)
- `POST /api/staged/` — create a staged request (any authenticated user)
- `GET /api/staged/` — list staged requests (own for users, all for admin; `?status=` and `?target_model=` filters)
- `GET /api/staged/{id}/` — detail view
- `POST /api/staged/{id}/approve/` — admin approves and applies the change to the DB
- `POST /api/staged/{id}/reject/` — admin rejects with optional note

### Authenticated (`/api/` — user-scoped)
- `GET/POST /api/highlights/` — list (filterable by ?subject=&chapter=) / create
- `DELETE /api/highlights/{id}/` — remove highlight
- `GET/POST /api/notes/` — list (filterable by ?subject=&chapter=) / create
- `GET/PATCH/DELETE /api/notes/{id}/` — read/update/delete note
- `POST /api/notes/{id}/analyze/` — AI analysis placeholder

### Documentation
- `GET /api/schema/` — OpenAPI 3.0 schema (YAML)
- `GET /api/docs/` — Swagger UI
- `GET /api/redoc/` — ReDoc

## Staged Request Flow

1. User/MCP calls `POST /api/staged/` with `{operation, target_model, target_id?, payload}`
2. Request is saved with `status=pending`
3. Admin reviews in Django Admin (color-coded status, JSON payload preview)
4. Admin approves → `StagedRequest.apply()` creates/updates/deletes the real model
5. Admin rejects → `StagedRequest.reject()` sets status + review note
6. MCP server uses staged requests for ALL write operations

## Conventions

### Adding a new model
1. Define in `chapters/models.py` with proper `Meta.ordering` and `__str__`
2. Register in `chapters/admin.py` with list_display, list_filter, search_fields
3. Create serializer in `chapters/serializers.py` — use camelCase field aliases for frontend compatibility
4. Add view in `chapters/views.py` with `@extend_schema` tags for Swagger docs
5. Add route in `chapters/urls.py`
6. Run `python manage.py makemigrations && python manage.py migrate`

### Serializer naming
- Read serializers: camelCase for JSON keys consumed by the frontend (e.g., `diagramCaption`)
- Write serializers: snake_case matching model fields for admin CRUD
- Map via `source=` parameter when needed

### Authentication
- JWT via djangorestframework-simplejwt
- Access token: 1 hour lifetime; refresh token: 14 days
- Public endpoints: `permission_classes = [AllowAny]`
- Authenticated endpoints: `permission_classes = [IsAuthenticated]`
- Admin endpoints: `permission_classes = [IsAdminUser]`
- User-scoped querysets: always filter by `user=self.request.user`

### CORS
- Allowed origins: localhost:5173, delta-learn.netlify.app
- Add new frontend domains to `CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS` in settings.py

### DeltaMails
- Topic pool: `EmailTopic` model seeded from chapters + AI-discovered via `refresh_topics`
- Dedup: `SentHistory` tracks every topic sent per subscription — no repeats until cycle reset
- Management commands:
  - `send_deltamails` — daily at 7 AM IST (django-crontab), picks topic, calls Gemma, sends email
  - `refresh_topics` — weekly on Mondays at 3 AM IST, AI generates ~20 new topics per subject
  - `seed_topics` — one-time seed from existing chapters
- Email: Apple-inspired full-bleed template, CID-attached PNG diagrams (via mmdc), per-subject accent
- Credentials in `.env`: GEMINI_API_KEY, GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD

